com.io7m.jtensors

Class VectorM2D

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.io7m.jtensors.VectorM2D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Vector2DType, VectorReadable2DType, VectorWritable2DType

    public final class VectorM2D
extends Object
implements Vector2DType

    A two-dimensional mutable vector type with double elements.

    Values of this type cannot be accessed safely from multiple threads without explicit synchronization.

    • Nested Class Summary

      static class  VectorM2D.ContextVM2D
      Preallocated storage to allow all vector functions to run without allocating.

      • interpolateLinear

        public static <V extends VectorWritable2DType> V interpolateLinear(VectorM2D.ContextVM2D c,
                                                                   VectorReadable2DType v0,
                                                                   VectorReadable2DType v1,
                                                                   double alpha,
                                                                   V r)
        Linearly interpolate between v0 and v1 by the amount alpha, saving the result to r. The alpha parameter controls the degree of interpolation, such that:
        • interpolateLinear(v0, v1, 0.0, r) -> r = v0
        • interpolateLinear(v0, v1, 1.0, r) -> r = v1
        Type Parameters:
        V - The precise type of writable vector
        Parameters:
        c - Preallocated storage
        v0 - The left input vector.
        v1 - The right input vector.
        alpha - The interpolation value, between 0.0 and 1.0.
        r - The result vector.
        Returns:
        r
        Since:
        7.0.0
